                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 419.11D29/70.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 19, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Supreme Court of Panama in the Fourth of July cases revokes decree of criminal
                    court reported by telegram of May 16th, but instead of ordering prosecutions
                    begun against somebody adjudges that the depositions of police regulations on
                    file are too vague and that Supreme Court itself shall reopen a full inquiry
                    having appointed one of the members to hold same and to report to the court.</p>
                <p>The most favorable outcome could only result in ordering prosecution begun by
                    lower court. I have been asked by Supreme Court judge if we would present again
                    for personal examination such of our witnesses as he might want later.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Price</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
